26/03/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- Police on Tuesday (25 March) arrested Muhamed Sacirbey, a former Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) foreign minister and ambassador to the UN. An international arrest warrant accuses him of stealing $2.5m from BiH's UN mission in New York. Sacirbey holds both BiH and US citizenship. Police found him at his home in Staten Island. A formal request for his extradition is expected Wednesday. (OHR Sources - 26/03/03; AFP - 25/03/03)
